<item>
<title>Exhibition at National Maritime Museum explores history of ship navigation</title>
<link>http://www.abc.net.au/pm/content/2016/s4457437.htm</link>
<description>This week's announcement from the US that marine archaeologists believe they've found the wreck of HMS Endeavour put the spotlight back on Australia's maritime history. When Captain Cook arrived here on the Endeavour in 1770, ship navigation was in the middle of a clock-driven revolution. A new exhibition at the Australian National Maritime Museum in Sydney explores that massive change. It's called Ships, Clocks and Stars - The Quest for Longitude.</description>

<item>
<title>Plane tracking system at Sydney Airport failing regularly</title>
<link>http://www.abc.net.au/pm/content/2016/s4454278.htm</link>
<description>A critical plane tracking system at Sydney Airport is failing regularly, leaving air traffic controllers deeply concerned about safety. The failures have so far not resulted in any major safety incidents but the air traffic controllers association, Civil Air, fears it's only a matter of time.</description>

<media:description>A critical plane tracking system at Sydney Airport is failing regularly, leaving air traffic controllers deeply concerned about safety. <title>Westpac profit hurt by rise in bad loans</title>
<link>http://www.abc.net.au/worldtoday/content/2016/s4454022.htm</link>
<description>Australia's second biggest bank Westpac has almost doubled its impairment charges for bad loans, hitting its first-half profit bottom line. Westpac's result rose 3 per cent to $3.7 billion. Concerns about charges for bad loans and a small rise in the bank's dividend saw Westpac shares fall more than 5 per cent in late morning trade.</description>

<media:description>Australia's second biggest bank Westpac has almost doubled its impairment charges for bad loans, hitting its first-half profit bottom line.
